Over the last few months, I've been
approached several times about the


2
0:0:22,239 --> 0:0:23,609
subject of death,


3
0:0:23,609 --> 0:0:28,46
including a tag by the wonderful Largo64, and the glorious Rozeboosje,


4
0:0:28,46 --> 0:0:30,73
enquires about psychological studies,


5
0:0:30,73 --> 0:0:33,379
assertions that I'm 'pro-mortality',


6
0:0:33,379 --> 0:0:36,91
questions about my responses to some
thought-terminating cliches,


7
0:0:36,91 --> 0:0:39,7
and about my personal outlook.


8
0:0:39,7 --> 0:0:42,5
I've always been fascinated by how we
cope with death --


9
0:0:42,5 --> 0:0:45,33
or more interestingly how we fail to
cope with it,


10
0:0:45,33 --> 0:0:48,95
with all the destructive consequences
those failures bring.


11
0:0:48,95 --> 0:0:52,5
It's also had some personal residence
for me recently.


12
0:0:52,5 --> 0:0:55,95
It feels the right time to share that I
started experiencing throat problems a few


13
0:0:55,95 --> 0:0:58,36
months ago that wouldn't go away.


14
0:0:58,36 --> 0:1:0,22
When I reported the symptoms,


15
0:1:0,22 --> 0:1:3,95
the doctors immediately suspected an
aggressive type of cancer that one of my


16
0:1:3,95 --> 0:1:7,82
brothers died of, and I was rushed
through a series of tests.


17
0:1:7,82 --> 0:1:10,909
I recently received the results of those
